The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, August 18, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 Bharat Electronics Ltd (BEL) has been ranked first among the mid-sized companies by a leading international journal. The journal, Aviation Week And Space Technology, published by Mcgraw Hill Publications, considered 42 companies with a turnover of less than $4 billion from the world over for the top-performing company rankings. The study analyses how well aerospace and defence firms employ their resources for growth.																								 Netafim Irrigation India Pvt Ltd, the Indian arm of the Israel-based drip irrigation system manufacturer, Netafim, would set up two drip irrigation producing facilities in Andhra Pradesh and Maharashtra at an investment of Rs 20 crore by 2005. We will set up two drip irrigation system manufacturing facilities to manufacture 10 crore metres of drip lines each by 2005, managing director ZVI Feler said.																								 Colgate-Palmolive (India) Ltd has launched Palmolive Aroma Sensual shower gel priced at Rs 90 for a 250 ml pack. The gel is enriched with a blend of orchid extract and essential oils of jasmine and rose.																								 ICI Paints has introduced Dulux TileShield, a tough, protective 100 per cent acrylic paint especially formulated for exterior tiles and bricks. Due to its special silicone-rich acrylic latex formula, Dulux TileShield, available in a range of dark colours, forms a tough, water-repellent paint film.																								 ICICI Lombard General Insurance Company, a leading private sector insurance company, has offered financial assistance by settling on-account insurance claims of Rs 1.12 crore on-the-spot to flood-affected industrial units, largely in the SME sector, at Silvasa, Daman and Surat in Gujarat and Patiala, Chandigarh and Ambala regions in the northern belt in Punjab and Haryana. 																								 Parryware, the sanitaryware division of EID Parry Limited, a Murugappa group company, has ventured into the taps market in Kerala with the launch of their entire range of taps and fittings. ADVERTISEMENT
